OL,3,CHealth minister needed 'a scapegoat,'
OL,4,Csays sacked health trust chair
OL,6,FResponding Health Minister Mike
OL,7,FNesbitt said he did not want to engage
OL,8,Fin a war of words and wished Mr
OL,9,FMulgrew well. He did, however, say he
OL,10,Fdid not recognise "a number of
OL,11,Fassertions made by Mr Mulgrew that he
OL,12,Fdid not recognise as fact". The MLA
OL,13,Fsaid he needed to have confidence in
OL,14,Fthe chair of the Belfast Trust and his
OL,15,Factions were in its best interests.
OL,17,FAccording to Mr Mulgrew, Minister
OL,18,FNesbitt first asked him to resign as
OL,19,Fhe would like a "soft landing".
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/11
