OL,3,CHealth minister needed 'a scapegoat,'
OL,4,Csays sacked health trust chair
OL,6,F"I told him that no, I didn't believe
OL,7,FI'd done anything wrong and that this
OL,8,Fwas a matter of principle and that if
OL,9,Fhe wanted to sack me, then he'd have
OL,10,Fto sack me," he said.
OL,12,F"Because from my point of view, I
OL,13,Fwasn't going to walk away and leave
OL,14,Fbehind the people within the Trust
OL,15,Fwho'd invested their hope and their
OL,16,Fsupport in me."
OL,18,FMr Mulgrew said this whole
OL,19,Fconversation happened in a Microsoft
OL,20,FTeams call and the minister did not
OL,21,Fturn on his camera to sack him.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/11
