OL,3,CHealth minister needed 'a scapegoat,'
OL,4,Csays sacked health trust chair
OL,6,F"I tried as best I could to resolve
OL,7,Fthose problems for people, and I think
OL,8,Fthe fact that the medical staff
OL,9,Fcommittee have been supportive of me
OL,10,Freflects the fact that I made efforts
OL,11,Fto do that.
OL,13,F"No one came to me with a problem that
OL,14,FI did not try to improve and I did not
OL,15,Ftry to deal with."
OL,17,FMr Mulgrew also said he does not think
OL,18,FMinister Nesbitt should remain in his
OL,19,Frole.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/11
