OL,3,CHealth minister needed 'a scapegoat,'
OL,4,Csays sacked health trust chair
OL,6,FHe said the minister fired him in the
OL,7,Fsame Teams call that he asked him to
OL,8,Fstay on and continue with an interview
OL,9,Fprocess for a new Chief Executive for
OL,10,Fthe Trust.
OL,12,F"I think there are a couple of reasons
OL,13,Ffor that. Firstly, if we take the
OL,14,Fissue whereby he goes against the
OL,15,Fadvice of his senior civil servant,
OL,16,Fthe permanent secretary, who advised
OL,17,Fhim not to dismiss me. Secondly, So
OL,18,Fthe minister sacked me on a call and
OL,19,Fon the same call asked me to interview
OL,20,Fand appoint a chief executive officer
OL,21,Ffor the trust.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/11
